aning of the word Chair which falls into the home category.";i:18;s:43:"You can also watch it as its being written.";i:19;s:71:"Click the audio buttons to know how to say Chair in Arabic and English.";i:20;s:41:"Chairthe person in charge of the meeting.";i:21;s:128:"Some people will say chairman and chairwoman or even chairperson but most people now just say chair for either a man or a woman.";i:22;s:52:"Chair can also be the action of leading the meeting.";i:23;s:42:"Call to orderthe chair starts the meeting.";i:24;s:41:"Im going to read a new book to you today.";i:25;s:24:"Its called Peters Chair.";i:26;s:76:"It uses some words you might not know so Im going to tell you the words now.";i:27;s:80:"Then when I read the story I want you to raise your hand when you hear the word.";i:28;s:49:"Tell students the three words and their meanings.";i:29;s:39:"Have them repeat the words back to you.";i:30;s:61:"In this lesson youll learn how to chair a meeting in English.";i:31;s:88:"You can learn business English words and phrases which you can use in your next meeting.";i:32;s:116:"An item of furniture used to sit on or in comprising a seat legs back and sometimes arm rests for use by one person.";i:33;s:51:"Compare stool couch sofa settee loveseat and bench.";i:34;s:96:"All I need to weather a snowstorm is hot coffee a warm fire a good book and a comfortable chair.";i:35;s:38:"Types of Chairs Vocabulary in English.";i:36;s:61:"Chairs are supported most often by four legs and have a back.";i:37;s:66:"However a chair can have three legs or can have a different shape.";i:38;s:211:"Chairs are made of a wide variety of materials ranging from wood to metal to synthetic material and they may be padded or upholstered in various colors and fabrics either just on the seat or on the entire chair.";i:39;s:271:"From Latin cathedra which in turn has its origin in a Greek word that means seat the chair is the particular matter or faculty that teaches a professor a teacher who has met certain requirements to teach knowledge and that he has reached the highest position in teaching.";i:40;s:79:"Classroom objects are the educational equipment and the objects in a classroom.";i:41;s:100:"The classroom objects can include stationery equipment teaching materials and other school supplies.";i:42;s:70:"Classroom objects are the basic English vocabulary to teach for every.";i:43;s:38:"Learn Furniture Vocabulary in English.";i:44;s:83:"Furniture includes objects such as tables chairs beds desks dressers or cupboardsv.";i:45;s:159:"Furniture refers to movable objects intended to support various human activities such as sitting eg chairs stools and sofas eating tables and sleeping eg beds.";i:46;s:91:"The definition of a chair is an official person or one who directs the course of a meeting.";i:47;s:57:"An example of a chair is the facilitator at a conference.";i:48;s:19:"To chair a meeting.";i:49;s:51:"Henry will be chairing the meeting when he is away.";i:50;s:58:"The meeting was chaired by Henry who welcomed the members.";i:51;s:54:"Chairing a meeting means to be in charge of a meeting.";i:52;s:50:"You need an object when you use the verb to chair.";i:53;s:23:"In this case a meeting.";i:54;s:34:"Meaning of to chair Pronunciation.";i:55;s:73:"Deciding vote usually by the chairman when the votes are otherwise equal.";i:56;s:70:"The role of treasurer was decided based on the chairmans casting vote.";i:57;s:46:"The person who leads or presides at a meeting.";i:58;s:50:"As chair it is my pleasure to introduce to you Mr.";i:59;s:53:"Welcome to the latest meeting for the Samuel Project.";i:60;s:126:"I appreciate that youre all busy and thanks for attendingMy name is David Mitchell and I will be the Chair for todays meeting.";i:61;s:42:"Steve Crowther will be taking the minutes.";i:62;s:69:"Youll find a copy of the meeting agenda in front of you on the table.";i:63;s:69:"As you can see there are 7 items which we are going to discuss today.";i:64;s:334:"From Longman 